name: cellulase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Endohydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in cellulose, lichenin and cereal beta-D-glucans
comment: Will also hydrolyse 1,4-linkages in beta-D-glucans also containing 1,3-linkages.
